/*  1240d - Adafruit Bluefruit LED Controller
 * 
 * This sketch shows you how to transmits values retrieved from your phones 
 * sensors and color picker to the Arduino. If you connect an RGB LED, you will 
 * be able to control it via the Adafruit Bluefruit app (available for iOS and Android).
 * 
 * 
 * This sketch uses software serial connection between the module and the Arduino.
 * Please see below for wiring information.
 * 
 * Once you have the connections completed, upload this sketch and start the Bluefruit app
 * on your phone. Connect to the Bluefruit module and navigate to the Controller view. Open
 * the serial monitor on the Arduino IDE.
 * 
 * Interact with the various widgets on the app, and notice how the values they produce 
 * are sent to the Arduino via the BLE connection.
 * 
 * This sketch was adapted by Peter Dalmaris for Arduino Step by Step from the original
 * sketch that was developed by Adafruit and ships with the Adafruit_BLE library.
 * 
 * Components
 * ----------
 *  - Arduino Uno
 *  - Adafruit Bluefruit64 BLE
 *  - 1 x RGB LED (commont cathode)
 *  - 3 x 330 Ohm resistors
 *  - Jumper wires
 *  
 *  Libraries
 *  ---------
 *  - SoftwareSerial
 *  - Adafruit_BLE
 *  - Adafruit_BluefruitLE_SPI
 *  - Adafruit_BluefruitLE_UART
 *
 * Connections
 * -----------
 * Arduino Uno and Bluefruit BLE:
 *  
 *  Arduino Uno   |   Bluefruit BLE
 *  ------------------------------
 *        -       |       DFU
 *        GND     |       GND
 *        -       |       RTS
 *        5V      |       VIN
 *        9       |       RXI
 *        10      |       TXO
 *        11      |       CTS
 *        12      |       MOD
 *        
 * Connect the anode of the LEDs to Arduino digital pins 5, 4 and 3 (red, 
 * green, blue) via their individual current limiting resistor, and the 
 * cathode to GND.

 *        
 *  Created on October 18 2017 by Peter Dalmaris
 * 
 */

